The position of I Hakase was held by a single appointee with an equivalent rank of {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|lt=Junior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade|ja|жӯЈдёғдҪҚдёӢ|1=Senior Seventh Rank|lt=Senior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade|12=draft|12=draft}}, making it the highest-ranking post among the various specialists within the Bureau of Medicine. Among the ten physicians employed, one with superior knowledge and experience was selected as I Hakase. The primary duties involved teaching various {{ill|medical prescriptions|ja|и–¬ж–№|12=draft|12=draft}} (yakuhЕҚ) and {{ill|pulse diagnosis texts|ja|и„ҲзөҢ|12=draft|12=draft}} (myakugyЕҚ) to the medical practitioners (еҢ»з”ҹ). Until the establishment of the position of {{ill|Onna I Hakase|ja|еҘіеҢ»еҚҡеЈ«|12=draft|12=draft}}, the I Hakase was also responsible for orally teaching obstetrics to 30 female physicians recruited from among official maidservants. Both male and female physicians were required to undergo monthly examinations.
In addition to {{ill|official salary|ja|дҪҚзҰ„|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|seasonal salary|ja|еӯЈзҰ„|12=draft|12=draft}}, the I Hakase received a one-time fee (жқҹи„©) of one piece of cloth from each entering medical student. According to a decree issued on February 18, {{ill|791|ja|е»¶жҡҰ10th year|12=draft|12=draft}}, the I Hakase was also granted four chЕҚ of {{ill|land allocated for official use|ja|иҒ·з”°|12=draft|12=draft}}.<ref>гҖҺ{{ill|Ruisan Sandai Kyaku|ja|йЎһиҒҡдёүд»Јж ј|12=draft|12=draft}}гҖҸ, Volume 15, "Provisions for Official Land, Rank Land, and Administrative Land."</ref>
