The position of I Hakase was held by a single appointee with an equivalent Rank of {{ill|Junior Seventh Rank|lt=Junior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade|ja|жӯЈдёғдҪҚдёӢ|1=Senior Seventh Rank|lt=Senior Seventh Rank, Lower Grade|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Junior Seventh Rank|13=User:Immanuelle/Senior Seventh Rank|qq=}}, making it the highest-Ranking post among the various specialists within the Bureau of Medicine. Among the ten physicians employed, one with superior knowledge and experience was selected as I Hakase. The primary duties involved teaching various {{ill|medical prescriptions|ja|и–¬ж–№|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/medical prescriptions|qq=}} (yakuhЕҚ) and {{ill|pulse diagnosis texts|ja|и„ҲзөҢ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/pulse diagnosis texts|qq=}} (myakugyЕҚ) to the medical practitioners (еҢ»з”ҹ). Until the establishment of the position of {{ill|Onna I Hakase|ja|еҘіеҢ»еҚҡеЈ«|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Onna I Hakase|qq=}}, the I Hakase was also responsible for orally teaching obstetrics to 30 female physicians recruited from among official maidservants. Both male and female physicians were required to undergo monthly examinations.
In addition to {{ill|official salary|ja|дҪҚзҰ„|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/official salary|qq=}} and {{ill|seasonal salary|ja|еӯЈзҰ„|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/seasonal salary|qq=}}, the I Hakase received a one-time fee (жқҹи„©) of one piece of cloth from each entering medical student. According to a decree issued on February 18, {{ill|791|ja|е»¶жҡҰ10е№ҙ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/791|qq=}}, the I Hakase was also granted four chЕҚ of {{ill|land allocated for official use|ja|иҒ·з”°|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/land allocated for official use|qq=}}.<ref>гҖҺ{{ill|Ruisan Sandai Kyaku|ja|йЎһиҒҡдёүд»Јж ј|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ruisan Sandai Kyaku|qq=}}гҖҸ, Volume 15, "Provisions for Official Land, Rank Land, and Administrative Land."</ref>
